# Trading Intelligence OS — environment variable template
# Rules: variable NAMES and comments only. Never put real values in this file.
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill values locally. Never paste secrets into chat/Git/logs.
# Intake gate: artifacts/reports/PRE_CODE_ENVIRONMENT_INTAKE_REPORT.md (2026-07-06)

# ── AI execution mode (harness + research lab + jobs runner) ───────────────
# Absent or "mock" (the default) = null provider, offline, no network, no spend.
# "real" requires TIOS_AI_PROVIDER plus that provider's key below, and is gated
# on operator spend authority (T-011-05/T-017-05). Any other value fails closed.
# The jobs runner always forces mock; run_research_lab_v0 rejects non-mock.
# TIOS_AI_MODE=            # mock | real
# TIOS_AI_PROVIDER=        # anthropic | openai | google (only read when TIOS_AI_MODE=real)

# ── WS8: AI benchmark providers ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Status: ALL DEFERRED (operator chose "Add later", 2026-07-06).
# The benchmark harness must run credential-less via the null provider (AD-11).
# Uncomment and fill in .env only when a real benchmark run is scheduled.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=          # exact official SDK variable re-verified at implementation time

# ── WS4: MLflow + DVC ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Status: FULLY LOCAL for the S1 prototype (operator choice, 2026-07-06).
# No credentials required. Remote tracking/storage variables are intentionally absent;
# they may be introduced only at a later gate if local mode proves insufficient.

# ── WS2: Market data ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Binance public Spot data requires NO credential for the canonical frozen dataset.
# Exchange sandbox/testnet keys: DEFERRED until a gate genuinely requires them.
# Live-trading, withdrawal-enabled, or real-money credentials: NEVER requested.

# ── Future data providers (DEFERRED / leave unset) ─────────────────────────
# These names are reserved so future agents do not re-ask the same intake
# questions. Do not uncomment until a later gate approves a specific vendor,
# spend limit, dataset, and license review.
# COINAPI_API_KEY=
# KAIKO_API_KEY=
# TARDIS_API_KEY=
# DATABENTO_API_KEY=

# ── Future exchange sandbox/testnet/demo access (DEFERRED / leave unset) ───
# Use only after an approved S3+ paper/demo architecture decision. Keys must be
# least-privilege, isolated, revocable, and never withdrawal-enabled. Do not use
# live/real-money keys here.
# BINANCE_SPOT_TESTNET_API_KEY=
# BINANCE_SPOT_TESTNET_API_SECRET=
# OKX_DEMO_API_KEY=
# OKX_DEMO_API_SECRET=
# OKX_DEMO_API_PASSPHRASE=

# ── Future private account/exchange integrations (HUMAN-GATED / leave unset)
# Public market data should remain credential-less where possible. Private
# account/trading credentials require venue eligibility, product availability,
# fee/terms review, and a new human approval gate before any code can read them.
# KRAKEN_API_KEY=
# KRAKEN_API_SECRET=
# COINBASE_CDP_API_KEY_NAME=
# COINBASE_CDP_PRIVATE_KEY=
